> Beach walks, moonlight swims, umbrellas in your drinks, warm sweet breezes: That's where we're going with this weeknight winner. Perfectly seared spiced pork chops are mounded with a juicy, tropical salsa made of mango, lime, scallion, and chiles. On the side: cumin-roasted carrots and buttery scallion-lime jasmine rice. It all comes together in about 30 minutes, leaving plenty of time to shake up a cocktail and start dreaming of your next getaway.

== Cumin-Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(separating whites from greens); mince whites. Pick half the @cilantro{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @cumin{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Scallion Rice ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a small #pot{} (medium pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}. Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a pinch of salt; bring to a boil.

Once boiling, cover and reduce to a simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Mango Salsa ==

While rice cooks, drain @mango{4%ounce}, discarding juice; roughly chop.

In a medium #bowl{}, combine mango, scallion whites, chopped cilantro, a squeeze of lime juice (two squeezes for 4 servings), a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

== Pork Chops ==

Pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} and let rest at least ~{3%minutes}.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Stir in scallion greens, @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), a squeeze of lime juice, and lime zest to taste. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice pork crosswise. Divide rice, pork, and carrots between plates. Squeeze over remaining lime juice to taste. Top pork with salsa and serve.